Reasoning: The paper proposes a novel logic-device based on multi-ferroic materials and magneto-electric effect, which involves both electrical and magnetic properties. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) which deals with bio-inspired computing and optimization algorithms. The paper also involves electron transport and magnetization dynamics, which suggests the sub-categories cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) and cs.EM (Electromagnetism). Additionally, the paper deals with spin logic and nano-magnets, which could fall under cs.MS (Materials Science) and cs.ES (Embedded Systems).
